      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "At last after two years of dis\ncussion and delay, dirt is to fly on\nthe $35Q,00O concrete bridge at\nMonroe street. The city council\nlast night adopted the recommen-\ndation of Prof. w. H. Burr that\nwork begin at once on the founda-\ntons for the piers and abutments\nwhile the condition of low water\nprevailed. The recommendation of\nthe board of works that day labor\nbe employed was also approved.\n\n\nCouncilmen Mohr and Lambert\nannounced that they were willing\nfor the foundations and fills at\neither end be made by day labor,\nbut served notice that they will\noppose building the superstructure\nby other than the contract plan."
    }
